      "description": "Paper, an envelope, a stamp. The person can be anyone: an old friend, a parent, a mentor you've lost touch with. The discipline of a handwritten letter - no delete key, no immediate send - changes what you say and how you say it. The thinking required to fill a page produces clarity that email never demands.",
