      },
      "description": "Your memory. No preparation needed. The story can be funny, embarrassing, or consequential - or all three. Children who know their parents as people - with a past, with stories, with moments of failure and luck - have better psychological resilience than those who only know them as functions. The story doesn't have to be impressive.",
      "why_it_works": "It has to be true. The telling is the thing.",
      "bookable": false,
