      "description": "Any bookshop or library - the constraint is choosing something genuinely unfamiliar: topology, Byzantine history, mycology, Ottoman poetry Most men in their 40s have narrowed their reading to things adjacent to what they already know. Reading something with no prior context - a field with its own vocabulary, assumptions, and way of seeing - is a specific kind of mental stretching that doesn't happen gradually.",
