      "description": "Whoever lives nearby - the loose gate hinge, the stuck drawer, the guttering that's been wrong for a year The offer is the unusual part. Most men in their 40s have the skills to fix a dozen things in their neighbours' homes and have never offered.",
      "why_it_works": "The act of noticing what someone else needs and acting on it without occasion or expectation produces a specific social warmth that is genuinely rare in most modern neighbourhoods.",
      "bookable": false,
      "seasonal": false,
      "experience_types": [
        "experiment"
      ]
